        <head xml:id="la30px-bbb181-Hd1e104">Proposition 25</head>
        <p xml:id="la30px-bbb181-d1e106"> Proposition 25 </p>
        <p xml:id="la30px-bbb181-d1e111"> 
          Wars against the Indians of the Indies have always been
          prohibited, ever since the first, when the Admiral first discovered them. The Spaniards
          never obeyed any instruction, provision, document, nor commandment from the kings
          whatsoever. If any royal letter or provision seemed to advocate for war, it was by
          iniquitous and most false information, supplied by tyrants, in order to steal and
          enslave—and get rich by the blood of—the Indians. This was warned by the kings, many times
          over, and later they wrote and commanded against it.
        </p>
      </div>
